<p>I am reading a file and am trying to print out the matches for two regular expressions separated by a disjunction. How can I print out both of the matches while keeping the disjunction?  </p>  <pre><code>open(my $fh, $ARGV[0]) or die "ARGV[0] not found!\n";  while(my $line = &lt;$fh&gt;){     if ($line =~ /(NNPS\S+)|(DT\S+ JJ\S+ JJ\S+ NN\S+)/){         print $line, "\n", $1,  "\n", $2     } } </code></pre>  <p>The input will be:</p>  <pre><code>NNPS/Helicopters MD/will NN/patrol DT/the JJ/temporary JJ/no-fly NN/zone IN/around NNP/New NNP/Jersey POS/'s </code></pre>  <p>And the output will be:</p>  <pre><code>Line 1 NNPS/Helicopters DT/the JJ/temporary JJ/no-fly NN/zone </code></pre>